    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Former humans or draugr who have been so deeply infected by the Rot that they are no longer truly undead — they exist in a state of living corruption. Their flesh is mottled black and grey, their movements jerky but purposeful. They have fragments of awareness, just enough to hunt and destroy. They appear in the Emberwell chamber alongside the Grave-Construct, drawn there by the concentration of Rot energy.</p>",
      "director": "<p><strong>ABILITIES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Corrupted Claw</strong> (Main, Melee, Might): T1 3 dmg; T2 6 dmg + poisoned EoNT (save ends); T3 9 dmg + poisoned (save ends) + Might test or clinging (cannot move away).</li><li><strong>Rot Spray</strong> (Main, Ranged 40ft, Reason): T1 2 poison; T2 4 poison + slowed EoNT; T3 6 poison + slowed and weakened EoNT.</li></ul><p><strong>FEATURES</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Rot-Infused:</strong> Immune to poison and disease. Resist cold 5 and necrotic 5.</li><li><strong>Hunger:</strong> +1 to attack rolls vs. bloodied (below half SP) targets.</li><li><strong>Corrupted Resilience:</strong> First time reduced below half SP, heals 4 SP as the Rot compensates.</li></ul><p><strong>TACTICS (BEAT 19):</strong> Rush toward Kaelen. Use Rot Spray to slow the party. Close to melee and Corrupted Claw. Work in pairs against isolated targets.</p>",
